<SLUG> BC-BKC-USCHOOP-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC LOOKING TO LAGUNA BEACH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC's chances of landing Laguna Hills High
swingman Travis Hanour could hinge on whether the Trojans sign his
friend and teammate, forward Chris Manker, who was offered a
scholarship this week.
</P>
<P>
   `If Chris goes to USC, it would be a big factor,'' Hanour said.
``We could live together and it would be a big difference.''
</P>
<P>
   Hanour is trying to decide between Arizona and USC. Officially,
he is also considering Utah and Oregon State.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Arizona and USC) are both right there,'' Hanour said. ``I'm
still confused. I'm trying to figure out after four years, where I
would get the best education and the best possibility to play pro
basketball afterward.''
</P>
<P>
   Manker is deciding between Oregon State and USC. Both schools
would like to redshirt the 6-foot-9 forward.
</P>
<P>
   Manker and Hanour left Wednesday for a recruiting trip to Oregon
State, though Hanour said he ``probably'' would not be interested
in playing for the Beavers. Manker visited USC on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   USC has a scholarship to offer Hanker following last week's
departure of point guard Rashad Jones and shooting guard Malachi
Thurston. Hanour had committed to USC in late February, before
changing his mind.
</P>
<P>
   He said he will make a decision early next week, possibly as
early as Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``Chris and I will probably make our decision together,'' Hanour
said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Women's basketball shakeup: USC women's basketball coach
Chris Gobrecht has decided to alter her coaching staff, reassigning
assistants Erika Lang-Montgomery and Traci Nemechek to
administrative jobs within the athletic department. Gobrecht will
hire two new assistants, possibly in the next two or three weeks.
Assistant coach Stacy McIntyre will remain on the staff.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
