<P>
   AFRICA-DIAMONDS (Undated) _ The value of diamonds, coupled with
the anonymity and portability of the stones _ millions of dollars
worth can be smuggled in a sock without triggering a metal detector
_ have made diamonds one of the most potent, and dangerous,
currencies of modern Africa. This article was reported by Alan
Cowell in Zambia and Belgium, Ian Fisher in Congo, Blaine Harden in
Angola and New York, Norimitsu Onishi in Sierra Leone and Congo,
and Rachel L. Swarns in Botswana. It was written by Mr. Harden.
