   Indonesia......................$2.70 billion
</P>
<P>
   China..............................$2.10 billion
</P>
<P>
   Korea..............................$2.05 billion
</P>
<P>
   Russia............................$1.90 billion
</P>
<P>
   Brazil.............................$1.60 billion
</P>
<P>
   Thailand........................$1.30 billion
</P>
<P>
   India...............................$1.05 billion
</P>
<P>
   Bangladesh..................$1.02 billion
</P>
<P>
   Mexico...........................$0.95 billion
</P>
<P>
   Source: World Bank.
</P>
<P>
   TOP 10 USERS OF IMF RESOURCES (through Jan. 31, 2000)
</P>
<P>
   Russia................................$10.80 billion
</P>
<P>
   Indonesia............................$7.46 billion
</P>
<P>
   Brazil...................................$6.40 billion
</P>
<P>
   Repbulic of Korea............$4.46 billion
</P>
<P>
   Argentina............................$3.12 billion
</P>
<P>
   Mexico..................................$3.09 billion
</P>
<P>
   Thailand..............................$2.50 billion
</P>
<P>
   Ukraine................................$1.99 billion
</P>
<P>
   Algeria................................$1.38 billion
</P>
<P>
   Philippines........................$1.33 billion
</P>
<P>
   Source: International Monetary Fund
</P>
