<HEADLINE>
RUSH OUT TO A GOLD-PANNING SPOT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Is there any place in the country I can pan for gold?
</P>
<P>
   _ K.M.L., E. Peoria, Ill.
</P>
<P>
   A: A Florida company has published maps you can use to pan for
gold in seven states.
</P>
<P>
   Big Ten sells six gold maps of California and the West Coast and
five more for Alabama, Georgia, Michigan, North Carolina and South
Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   Individual maps sell for $12 with the exception of Alabama and
South Carolina, which sell for $12 as a set. Shipping and handling
is $3 regardless of how many maps you purchase.
</P>
<P>
   To order, write to Big Ten, Box 321231-W, Cocoa Beach, FL
32932-1231, or visit the Web site www.goldmaps.com.
</P>
<P>
   The closest gold-panning sites to Fort Worth-Dallas are in
Alabama and Georgia, said map creator Charles Overbey. ``Usually
people will find specks, but sometimes you don't find anything the
first time you're out,'' he said. ``It's a fun outing.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Why do airplane windows have tiny little scratches on them?
</P>
<P>
   _ W.D., Ramona, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   A: Most small hairline scratches and ``spider-webby'' marks you
see on airplane windows are caused when they are cleaned, said Jeff
Pfister, director of marketing for LP Aero Plastics, a manufacturer
of windows for corporate planes. ``The windows are made of plastic,
and not as hard as glass and get scratched as a matter of course.''
</P>
<P>
   Though scratches can be caused by cleaning brushes, a more
common cause is exposure to chemicals. ``Even things like volcanic
ash in the upper atmosphere can cause that,'' Pfister said.
</P>
<P>
   There's nothing unsafe about those scratches on the windows,
which are periodically removed and polished to remove the
scratches, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Q: A few years ago, you printed an address for the Barry Manilow
Fan Club. They took my money and never sent any information. Where
can I contact them?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.S., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Send your letter and proof of payment to Vicky Thomas, Barry
Manilow International Fan Club, Box 45378, Los Angeles, CA 90045.
</P>
<P>
   The club, which has 60,000 members and is the singer's official
fan club, offers $10 yearly memberships and sends out a quarterly
newsletter.
</P>
<P>
   The Better Business Bureau of the Southland has no complaints on
file against the club for the past three years and gives it a
``clear record'' rating. If you are not able to get a refund or
membership, you can file a complaint with that bureau by calling
(909) 825-7280.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
