r e BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE-C     04-06 0319
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Vince Russo and Eric Bischoff will have a lot of new faces to
work with when they put together their first ``Nitro'' show Monday.
Kevin Nash had the cast removed from his broken ankle and could
return to the ring in a month. ``Hard Knox'' Chris Candido has
signed a contract with WCW after a month of tryouts. No word on
whether the former ECW star's valet _ Tammy Lynn Sytch, a.k.a.
Sunny from her WWF days _ will be joining him.
</P>
<P>
   Goldberg and Rick Steiner may be back sooner. It appears
Goldberg may have been influential in getting Bischoff back in the
good graces of Time-Warner and Brad Siegel.
</P>
<P>
   Some other changes are on the way at WCW. Kevin Sullivan might
have a very short future. The man in the middle of The Radicals
departure has been offered a buyout on his contract. Meanwhile,
Russo's former WWF partner Ed Ferarra will be running things
backstage.
</P>
<P>
   WCW spin doctors are working the Internet getting out news on
Hulk Hogan. They are saying that Hogan refused to cleanly defeat
The Wall on ``Nitro'' because he felt it would end Wall's push as a
dominanting monster. So he asked that his ``new best buddy''
Vampiro do a run-in to save Hogan. This appears to be an attempt to
squash the anti-Hogan fans who feel he will do anything to keep the
young talent down and push himself to the top. Fans of the Tommy
Dreamer-Raven-dominated ECW should watch the next two TNN shows.
Tapings last week had Dreamer-Raven-Sandman in a classic ECW match
against the Baldies. Some of the foreign objects used included a
ladder, barbed wire, chairs and tables. The match ended with Mike
Awesome hitting the ring and decimating everyone. That leads to an
Awesome-Rhino match that is sure to please, although Awesome
retains the title.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
