<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-06 16:50 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9016 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l BC-TRAVEL-SEATTLE09-COX     04-06 0266
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-SEATTLE09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    If you're inclined to enjoy the city's flavor, hilltop
neighborhood is perfect
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, April 9.
 &HT;    By Jay Croft
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE _ Like all great cities, this Pacific Northwest
metropolis comprises a series of thriving neighborhoods, little
towns themselves that make the whole greater than the sum of its
parts.
</P>
<P>
   Many of Seattle's famous places are already etched into every
traveler's consciousness, such as the Space Needle and Pike Place
Market.
</P>
<P>
   But visit Capitol Hill for a different, eye-opening take on the
vital, energizing Emerald City. It's not the highlight of the tour
maps, but neither is it so strange that it's unwelcoming to
visitors. Capitol Hill is an appealing mishmash of the youth scene,
the gay community, liberal arts colleges, parks, shopping and
moviegoing.
</P>
<P>
   As any Seattle resident will tell you, this neighborhood up the
hill from downtown is ideal for a great day of hanging out,
traipsing from coffee shop to movie house, from bookstore to ethnic
restaurant. Capitol Hill combines the best elements of Atlanta's
Midtown, Virginia-Highland and Little Five Points _ with some of
the finest views of the city amid all the greenery and glimpses of
Elliott Bay and other surrounding bodies of water.
</P>
<P>
   By all means, order one of those ubiquitous espressos Seattle is
known for. You'll want to stay sharp for our walking tour.
</P>
<P>
   Jay Croft writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-06-00 1650EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT20000406.0240 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-06 16:50 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
