   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Hour after hour, day after day, the dump
trucks and tractor-trailers have rumbled west on Interstate 30 to a
privately run landfill on the rolling prairie near the
Tarrant-Parker county line. Overflowing with reminders of the March
28 storms, the trucks have disgorged tons of glass, roofing
shingles, old-growth trees, and bent and broken remnants of homes.
It's enough rubbish, so far, to cover a football field, end zone to
end zone, more than 20 feet deep. By CHRIS VAUGHN. Story has moved
in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
