in late 1999.
</P>
<P>
   According to Greek newspapers, the benchmark stock index must
return to the lofty 6000 level before PASOK will hold general
elections. (The index peaked at 6188 in September 1999 and sat
around 5100 in mid-January.)
</P>
<P>
   Without a guard as vigilant as the Securities and Exchange
Commission, you can't rule out some stock manipulation to get
