<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Friday, April 7 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, please contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News at
(818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   SUPNAT-AGREEMENT (Los Angeles) _ State regulators have
negotiated a reinsurance agreement with Kemper Insurance Companies
to provide financial support for new and renewal insurance policies
being written by Superior National Insurance Group Inc. By Chris
Sieroty.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-TECH (Los Angeles) _ Parade a series of fashion models
in front of an exhibit hall full of techies and you're bound to
draw a crowd. Put your products on those models, and you might just
get them noticed. For Sherman Oaks-based Charmed Technology, the
marriage of fashion and technology is more than just a gimmick to
get noticed, however. It's the basis of the company. By Jason
Cohen.
