<P>
   ELIAN-CUBA (Havana) _ In general, atmospherics in Cuba over
little Elian Gonzalez have quieted down, in contrast to the
intensity in Miami, at least among the diehard Elian minority
there. By Richard Chacon 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   US-HAITI (Boston) _ Secretary of State Madeleine K. Albright
says the Clinton administration ``is very disappointed'' with the
political violence and deferral of democracy in Haiti, and has been
unsuccessful in getting former President Jean Bertrand Aristide to
help ease the situation. By Charles A. Radin. 800 words.
</P>
