   CUBA-BOY (Washington) _ Efforts are under way to transfer
custody of 6-year-old Cuban refugee Elian Gonzalez to his father,
who is staying at a house in Bethesda, Md. By Anne E. Kornblut.
1200 words. (a and i coding)
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO-RULES (Boston) _ Massachusetts defends its tough
restrictions on cigarette advertising in federal court. The state
will argue that a lower court ruling in January upholding the
regulations should stand. Major cigarette manufacturers will
counter that the attorney general's stance violates free speech and
that any state regulations based on health and smoking is
pre-empted by federal law. By Frank Phillips. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   NEWBORN-SURGERY (Boston) _ In a complex operation with huge
technical and ethical challenges, doctors from two hospitals save a
premature baby by operating while she is half-out of the womb. by
Richard Saltus. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   LEWIS-TRIAL (Boston) _ A former intern for Dr. Gilbert Mudge
testifies for the first time that Mudge did -- as he claims -- have
a second, unpublicized diagnosis for Celtic star Reggie Lewis that
pointed to a serious heart condition. By Sacha Pfeiffer. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   GENOME-SEQUENCE (Undated) _ Celera Genomics says it has
sequenced a human gene map. Government experts cast doubt on the
announcement. Completion of a human genome map is still years away.
By Richard Saltus. 800 words.
</P>
