   VENEZUELA-OIL (Caracas) _ Since President Hugo Chavez took
office 14 months ago, this South American nation of 23 million
people, the largest producer of oil outside the Middle East and the
leading supplier to the United States in recent years, has gone
from lamb to lion on oil matters. By Larry Rohter.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-POLITICS (St. Petersburg, Russia) _ As President-elect
Vladimir Putin flew north beyond the Arctic circle this week to
ride a nuclear powered submarine and burnish his image as
commander-in-chief, the event that was making political waves was
the scuttling of his hand-picked candidate for governor of his home
region here. In a humbling concession by Putin to the political
strength and popularity of the incumbent governor, Vladimir
Yakolev, the new Russian president on Tuesday recalled Valentina
Matviyenko, his first deputy prime minister, from her vacation and,
according to Ms. Matviyenko, asked her to pull out of the race she
had entered with the Kremlin's blessing less than a month ago. By
Patrick E. Tyler.
</P>
