<P>
   NH-SUPREME-COURT (Concord, N.H.) _ Add to the casualty list of
collateral destruction by horrible divorces: the New Hampshire
State Supreme Court. One of the five justices, the divorcing one,
resigned last week in a deal that let him avoid criminal charges of
using improper influence. The chief justice had to hold a news
conference to defend his actions in the case. And despite a huge
backlog, the court has temporarily closed down shop to decide how
to respond to the crisis. The attorney general has released reports
saying the justices routinely comment on cases from which they had
recused themselves because of a possible conflict of interest. The
legislature is expected to vote next week on whether to begin
investigating impeachment of one or more of the justices. By Carey
Goldberg.
</P>
