   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   CONVENTIONS-MEDIA (Undated) _ The quadrennial political
conventions traditionally have served as a kind of national
show-and-tell for the broadcast network news divisions, an
opportunity for news stars to roam convention floors for immense
blocks of prime time and impress viewers with the breadth and depth
of their political reportage. But now, the approach to the
proceedings is merely one more example of the radical shift in
election coverage on television. While the broadcast networks are
looking for ways to pare down their coverage, CNN and its nearly
equally politics-driven rivals on cable, C-Span, MSNBC and Fox News
Channel, have usurped the role of the old broadcast networks as the
dominant conveyance for the nation's political news. By Peter
Marks.
</P>
