<HEADER>
A9237 &Cx1f; tth-z
u v BC-BUDGET-SPI &LR;      04-06 0384
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Friday, April 7, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Bob Schenet on the national-foreign desk at (206) 448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   TERROR-BOUNTY (Undated) _ State Department offers $5 million for
the arrest and capture of Ahmed Ressam's alleged Algerian
accomplice, Dahoumane, who was indicted along with Ressam in the
alleged bomb plot that, among other things, caused Seattle to scrub
its New Years Eve gala.
</P>
<P>
   By Sam Skolnik. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-RETURN (Undated) _ ``Return to Me'' carries no surprises
but floats nicely on the simple charm of innocent romance and the
good company of endearing characters. It's not quite magic, but
it'll do until the real thing comes along.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-RULES (Undated) _ ``Rules of Engagement'' opens with two
devastating action sequences, but it's downhill from there. By the
time the film plummets to its rock bottom, we find ourselves in a
flag-waving no-brainer of the first order, and one of the most
thoroughly confused morality tales in recent memory.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-RUMBLE (Undated) _ ``Ready to Ruble'' begins as an idiot
comedy with gross-out gags. But when it loses the
anything-for-a-laugh excess, there's little left. Real professional
wrestling has become such a circus of outrageous stunts and soap
opera mythology that this winds up less parody than pale imitation.
</P>
<P>
   By Sean Axmaker. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-PRESIDENTS (Undated) _ Anyone who has tried to memorize the
presidents of the United States in chronological order will be
frustrated by PBS's ``The American President.'' But in fact, the
10-hour documentary series, running two hours each night from
Sunday through Thursday, is a mostly pleasant departure from the
numerical, ``name-the-16th-president'' style we may remember from
grade school.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-MASTERS (Augusta, Ga.) _ First round play at the Masters.
</P>
<P>
   By Dan Raley. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Seattle) _ Seattle Mariners host Boston Red Sox.
</P>
<P>
   By John Hickey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
