<SLUG> BC-HIGH-POINT07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Super recliner an easy-does-it hit
 &HT;    By Danny C. Flanders
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   HIGH POINT, N.C. _ What comes out of this normally sleepy
Piedmont town over the next seven days will dictate what you will
buy, or at least, want for your home right now.
</P>
<P>
   Like the fashion shows that control what we wear, the world's
largest furniture market, held here each spring and fall, controls
how we nest.
</P>
<P>
   So, what are the emerging ``must-haves'' after Day One?
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Chintz Charming. What better way to title a press luncheon
where New York designer Mario Buatta, aka ``The Prince of Chintz,''
rolled out his new collection for John Widdicomb Co. as 70,000
retailers and interior designers poured into town on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The eight pieces, reflecting New York 1930s glamour, include a
cocktail table, drawer chest, sofas, chairs and ottomans, with
subtle fabric designs.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's like someone came through with the chintz repellent,''
said the comical Buatta, known to lighten his design talks with
such antics as tipping his toupee to the audience. ``But decorating
always follows fashion, and everything's cleaner here.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Lazy surfing. La-Z-Boy and Microsoft subsidiaries WebTV
Networks wowed shoppers with their ``E-Cliner,'' a chair with all
the plush comfort of a recliner but with an arm-attached keyboard
that allows the occupant to surf the Web, send e-mails, watch TV
and plan their show lineup without sitting at a desk (left).
Expected retail: $1,049. ``Reaction has been phenomenal,'' La-Z-Boy
spokeswoman Kay Degenhardt said.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Hemingway's Paris. Thomasville Furniture has added a new group
to its Ernest Hemingway Collection of pieces inspired by the
author's homes and travels.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Alexander Julian. The Home Improvement Warehouse is bringing
fashion and furnishings designer Julian aboard with a new
do-it-yourself decorating program for the chain using _ you guessed
it _ Julian's lamps, rugs and wallpapers.
</P>
<P>
   Danny C. Flanders writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
