 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)  
 &HT;    Speeding up your processor can be risky
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ www.overclockin.com _ Now that semiconductor
companies have hit the one-gigahertz mark, is it time to throw away
your old processor and upgrade? Not according to this site, which
offers news and information about overclocking, a risky and
dangerous way to speed up your existing central processing unit by
changing motherboard and system settings. It's controversial and
may fry your system, so overclock at your own risk.
</P>
<P>
   www.wisecity.com _ What's a FreeAger? According to this new
site, it's a savvy Internet user over the age of 45 who knows what
he or she wants and who needs a Web site to help them find it.
Started up by John Ryan, the site includes news, travel information
and lots of other services.
</P>
<P>
   www.eyada.com _ If you still aren't tired of the fallout from
the ``Who Wants to Marry a Multimillionaire'' show, this site will
entertain you: Rick, our hapless multimillionaire, has allowed this
site to seek out a new bride by posting their photos and short
descriptions on ``Rick's Gallery of Love.'' Sad, terrible and a
little bit entertaining.
</P>
<P>
   www.dogware.com/1040-DOG.htm _ Just in time for tax season: The
U.S. Individual Canine Income Tax Return is a tax form for dogs.
It's funny. Trust us.
</P>
