 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; THERE'S NO BUSINESS LIKE FAMILY BUSINESS &LR;
<P>
   &UR; Jerry Seinfeld  &LR; and  &UR; Jessica Sklar  &LR; are expecting a baby in
December, a bit of news the comedian had  &UR; Regis Philbin  &LR; announce
on Thursday, April 6's ``Live With Regis &AMP; Kathie Lee'' show.
Meanwhile,  &UR; Kathie Lee Gifford &LR; 's son  &UR; Cody &LR; , 10, is suing the
National Examiner, a tabloid, for saying he acted like a brat
during a film shoot, reports Wireless Flash.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Nicolas Cage  &LR; has withdrawn the petition he filed six weeks ago
to divorce &UR; Patricia Arquette &LR; , although that petition had said the
couple separated in 1996.
</P>
<P>
   And  &UR; Annette Bening &LR; , surrounded by physicians and unable to
ascend the stairs to the stage at the Oscars because of her
delicate condition, isn't due to have her baby until next week,
says her publicist. Were all the Oscar precautions p.r. hoo-ha?
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; CELEBRITY LITERATURE FOR THE WEE READERS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; He may not be up to ``War and Peace,'' but there's no reason
 &UR; John Travolta &LR;  can't write literature for young readers. Travolta's
``Propeller One-Way Night Coach'' (Warner; $12.98), written and
illustrated by the actor, is one of a flock of children's books
written by celebrities. ``Kids' books have a special appeal,''
Random House editor  &UR; Jonathan Karp &LR;  told Forbes FYI. ``They're
short, with big type, and you get paid.''
</P>
<P>
   Among Travolta's fellow travelers in the field: The  &UR; Duchess &LR; 
 &UR; of York &LR; ,  &UR; Mary-Chapin Carpenter &LR; ,  &UR; Shaquille O'Neal &LR; ,  &UR; Patrick &LR; 
 &UR; Ewing &LR; ,  &UR; Jamie Lee Curtis &LR; ,  &UR; Debby Boone  &LR; and  &UR; Jane Seymour &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   One of the Travolta book's scenes, as described in a clip
forwarded to Personals by  &UR; Angela Weber &LR; : ``Just prior to the
story's climax, a drugged mental patient on board the plane
suddenly comes to and attacks the flight attendant. `The man had
his hands around the throat of the young lady and she had her hands
around his throat as well.'''
</P>
<P>
   Forbes FYI's comment: ``Times change. Good night, moon.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; THE ROYAL TREATMENT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _In Greenland, 310 miles south of the North Pole,  &UR; Queen &LR; 
 &UR; Margrethe &LR;   &UR; II  &LR; of Denmark visited her son,  &UR; Prince Frederik &LR; , 30,
who is making a 2,170-mile dogsled trek with five other members of
the Danish Navy. He made her a cup of coffee from melted snow; she
brought him ``a most exquisite'' almond cake, said another member
of the expedition.
</P>
<P>
   _The London Mirror ran three pages of pictures of  &UR; Camilla &LR; 
 &UR; Parker Bowles &LR;  in a swimsuit and noted that her legs are
``cellulite-free.'' Meanwhile,  &UR; Prince William &LR; , 17, went on a
school trip to the north of England and performed ``YMCA'' in a
karaoke bar.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; TABLE-HOPPING &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _Biography magazine asked: ``If you were stranded on a desert
island and could have any restaurant in the world open a branch
there, which would you choose? ``The French Laundry in Napa Valley,
California,'' said  &UR; John Lithgow &LR; . ``Anyone who has been there
knows why I chose that. It's absolutely the greatest restaurant
I've ever been to. My dish? Anything but fish.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; _Dining out in New York recently, Vogue editor  &UR; Anna Wintour &LR;  sent
her steak back to the kitchen three times, reports the New York
Daily News, because it wasn't raw enough.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``As I move into my late 40s and 50s I am going to be wearing &LR; 
 &UR; a lot more suit-and-ties, because that is what's appropriate for &LR; 
 &UR; that age. ... You don't want to be that a_ in the safari jacket &LR; 
 &UR; with one strand of hair wrapped around his head quoting Dylan &LR; 
 &UR; Thomas and trying to impress the girls.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Bill Maher &LR;  in Gear magazine.
