demanding a halt to ``endless, confusing procedures'' in U.S.
courts. (Rick McKay/Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) HYDE PARK, Mass. -- April 6, 2000 -- WEB-HAGGLERS-BOS --
Denise Mowles plays with her three-year old daughter Fallon with
some of the items she has purchased online. Mowles, who in the past
has successfully bargained with big retail outfits for a cheaper
televison and video camera, now bids and shops online for
everything from Beanie Babies to Disney clothes for her children.
(Bill Greene/The Boston Globe)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) WASHINGTON -- April 6, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., APRIL 9 --
GORE-HYPE -- Bob Somerby delights in boxing the ears of reporters
inside the Beltway with his Web site, The Daily Howler, a biting
critique of press coverage, especially of the presidential campaign
of Vice President Al Gore, Somerby's roommate at Harvard. (Rick
McKay/Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) UNDATED -- April 6, 2000 -- ART-NOTES -- Christie's in
London seems to be getting some of Europe's greatest collections to
sell this summer. Included in the July auction will be Rubens oil
sketch, ``Diana and Her Nymphs Hunting.'' (Christie's/The New York
Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) ROCKVILLE, Md. -- April 6, 2000 -- HUMAN-GENOME -- Celera
Genomics, a private company striving to map the human genetic code,
reported Thursday that it has completed a major step in the project
-- decoding the pieces of DNA that make us what we are. J. Craig
Venter, president of Celera, in 1999 showing a room which contains
computers used in the decoding project. (Marty Katz/The New York
Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) UNDATED -- April 6, 2000 -- GENERAL-SEX-CHARGE -- Maj.
Gen. Larry G. Smith, accused of sexual harassment by the Army's
highest-ranking woman, is seen in an undated photo. Smith's
appointed last August to be the service's deputy inspector general,
an officer responsible for investigating accusations of wrongdoing,
including sexual misconduct, has been frozen while the Army's
inspector general investigates the accusation by Lt. Gen. Claudia
J. Kennedy that Smith made an unwanted sexual advance in her office
at the Pentagon, officials said. (Department of Defense/The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) WASHINGTON -- April 6, 2000 -- CUBAN-BOY -- Juan Miguel
Gonzalez carries his six-month-old son Hianny as his wife Nercy
Carmenate Castillo is assisted in leaving a jet that carried them
from Cuba to Dulles International Airport, Thursday. In the hour
after sunrise, the jet carrying the father of Elian Gonzalez
touched down in an airport near Washington, D.C., where Gonzalez
vowed to take his son back to Cuba. (Paul Hosefros/The New York
Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) WASHINGTON -- April 6, 2000 -- CLINTON -- President
Clinton is followed by his mother-in-law Dorothy Rodham after
arriving on Marine One to the White House following an overnight
visit to Chappaqua, N.Y. Thursday. Clinton did not respond to
questions from reporters regarding the Elian Gonzalez custody
issue. (Stephen Crowley/The New York Times)
