 &UR; YOUTHS: &LR;  Selling ice cream on a cold, miserable windy night at 3Com
Park is a vendor's worst nightmare. Muma Okochi knew he had to come
up with an unusual pitch last year to get the attention of the
baseball fans. That's when the teenager hit upon the idea. ``I got
creative, yelling things like `Get your nice hot ice cream!' It got
people's attention, and it showed me that the job can be what you
make of it.'' For Okochi, the invaluable work experience as well as
the assistance he got landing an academic scholarship to attend the
University of California at Berkeley this fall has come through the
efforts of a San Francisco nonprofit organization called Juma
Ventures.  &UR; BY JENNIE YABROFF &LR;
