<SLUG> BC-TEN-DAVISIDE-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MCENEROE STILL FIRING VERBAL VOLLEYS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LEE BARNATHAN  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ Boldly predicting a United States Davis Cup
victory over the Czech Republic isn't the only strong opinion John
McEnroe voiced this week. On the occasion of this, his first time
captaining the U.S. team on American soil, McEnroe was outspoken.
Some things never change.
</P>
<P>
   Besides railing against the Cup schedule, in which nations play
four weekends spread out over a calendar year (he thinks the
schedule should be condensed), and praising Pete Sampras for
joining the team, McEnroe said being Davis Cup captain isn't fun.
</P>
<P>
   ``Fun is not the word I would use to describe it, but at the
same time, because I believe in it, I think it's worth it,''
McEnroe said. ``The fun is when (Chris) Woodruff hit that ace on
match point (in Zimbabwe in February). Then there's that moment
when you hug and rally around each other, and there's this joy for
a few minutes.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a great moment, then everyone goes their separate
ways.''
</P>
<P>
   Nor was it pleasant when McEnroe had to call Woodruff and tell
him he won't play in this weekend's quarterfinal. Woodruff
originally wasn't playing in the first round, either, but he filled
in for an injured Sampras.
</P>
<P>
   ``You feel bad that you have to tell someone who obviously had
the greatest moment of his career, `Thanks a lot, but keep ready,'
'' McEnroe said. ``He's sitting in Tennessee feeling like he's not
part of it. He, in all likelihood, would be the guy I call once
someone couldn't play.''
</P>
<P>
   One place McEnroe didn't venture an opinion was to say if this
team, with top-ranked Agassi and No. 2 Sampras is better than the
'92 team featuring Agassi, Sampras . . . and McEnroe.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not going to answer that. I'm captain,'' he said. ``If I
were a player, I'd have a different answer.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
